We use Components to indicate the various teams involved in a project (Reporting, Web, CRM, etc.).  Therefore, we are careful to use the same component names across projects as we hope for a fix for JRA-8663.  It's useful to us to use the Two-Dimensional Filter Statistics widget to report on the state of issues across the various projects in a release, but I realized that, with Component on the X-axis, the widget treats each component from each project individually, rather than combining like-named components into a single column.  I would like the option to be made available (probably as a checkbox) to group like-named columns or rows together.  In the case of the Component field, the JQL would go from "project in (PROJ1,PROJ2,PROJ3) AND component = 'Reporting' AND project = PROJ1" to just "project in (PROJ1,PROJ2,PROJ3) AND component = 'Reporting'".

