This would be especially useful for transitions that have no entry screen, as for those transitions, it's very easy to accidentally click on the wrong place on the screen and transition an issue forward by mistake.

We have some transitions that make no sense to be able to reverse once they've sat for a while, as they will set off other actions that can't be easily  be undone.  For that reason, we don't want to put a reverse step in as a formal part of our workflow.  But it would be nice to have a way to allow the user to immediately say "I didn't mean to do that".  Even if that action couldn't be time-limited, users could be instructed that that feature is only to be used to immediately reverse a mistake.

