We have a workflow that has many steps that can't be reversed.  For these, the only time it makes sense to go back to the prior step is if the user moved the issue forward by mistake.

Rather than putting these "Oops, I screwed up" transitions in our workflow, we'd rather that the user have to go to an administrator to fix the problem.  And in general, we'd like a feature where an admin or other superuser could change the status of an issue to ANY other value regardless of the workflow.

So, please add a super-user feature, to be used only in exceptional cases, where the status on an issue could be changed to any value.

